              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Original research, comprehensive guides, free tools and calculators, templates, and infographics with original data. Content that saves the reader significant time and cannot easily be found elsewhere performs best.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How many links should a good resource page have?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Effective resource pages typically contain 10-100 well-curated links. Pages with fewer than 10 links are too thin. Pages with hundreds of links dilute the value passed per link and often look more like link farms than curated resources.</p></div></div>
